5. Key Scoring Rules (Do Not Reinterpret)
Response Encoding
Response
Value
No
0
Somewhat
1
Yes
2

Percentages
Stored as decimals (0.00 – 1.00)


Never as 0–100


Stage Fit Logic
variance = maturity_pct – urgency_normalized

< -0.15  → Below
-0.15 to +0.15 → At
> +0.15 → Ahead

Band Assignment Rule
pct >= min_pct AND pct <= max_pct

Max maturity band uses max_pct = 1.01 to capture perfect scores.

6. Known Design Decisions (Intentional)
Scoring is NOT reactive
 It runs once per submission to avoid partial or inconsistent states.


SQL over views
 Ensures deterministic scoring and prevents “live recalculation drift.”


Ordering table exists on purpose
 gm_checkpoint_stage_dimension_order provides a fallback ranking when urgency and response tiers tie.


IDs vs labels


Tables store IDs


Labels are joined later for reporting / GPT


Do not bake labels into logic



7. QA Queries the Next Assistant Should Use
